figures, but certainly above $30,000 a year. Do 
you have any figures or any estimate on what

30:06.247 --> 30:13.835
percent of students in the engineering college 
are in the civil engineering department? Well, I

30:13.855 --> 30:15.456
can pull out some figures in a hurry. Last fall, 
there were, let's say, 1,200 students in civil,

30:15.937 --> 30:29.491
and there were 10,500 approximately students in 
the college. Now, those are not all engineering

30:30.512 --> 30:32.694
students. There are some degree programs in the 
College of Engineering that are not engineering,

30:35.930 --> 30:40.135
not programs leading to bachelor's degree in 
engineering. That's total, the undergraduate

30:40.155 --> 30:42.178
and graduate. So whatever 1,200 is as a percent of 
